file_content.text: Talk to Agent Madel. We'll finish up in here.
Go through the building. Bring me any information on the extent of this rebellion.
I will respect your decision, but if these aliens continue to strike against the Empire, know that I will not fail to act.
I don't think the Flame will be bothering the Empire again.
He's learned his lesson.
I hope we can rely on your judgment, then.
Do as you must.
You're right. And do not doubt that I will do what is necessary to protect the Empire.
You don't want to make me your enemy.
Don't defy me.
A difference of opinions does not make us enemies. So long as your support for these rebels ends here.
A disagreement does not make us enemies, my lord. I shall abide by your call.
We are not enemies. So long as your support for the rebels does not extend beyond today.
Make your report to Agent Madel. I will let you explain how things came to end this way.
I was fortunate to have you here, my friends.
It was my fortune and my honor to have you here, my lord.
When I asked you to accompany me, I didn't know I would end up owing you my life.
I'll call Agent Madel and tell her what happened. I suggest you make the full report.
My men and I will stay here to ensure the Gen'Dai's body is destroyed.
Without him, the aliens' rebellion should fall quickly.
We have won this war.
I'm certain Agent Madel will be able to mop up any resisters.
The Flame was a strong man. He should have been serving us, not fighting us.
His death is a loss.
The Empire has no place for such monstrosities.
Will you make the transfer, or does Agent Madel handle that?
What about my payment?
Don't worry, bounty hunter. The Empire will make sure you're well-compensated.
I'll make the report.
Thank you for your service.
We are supposed to meet the Hutts in a few minutes time. We shall talk then.
